article.description: Arkansas St. beats Cent. Ark. in a 99-56 blowout
article.headline: Arkansas St. beats Cent. Ark. in a 99-56 blowout
article.linkText: Arkansas St. beats Cent. Ark. in a 99-56 blowout
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- Kirk Van Slyke scored 23 points and had nine rebounds as Arkansas State beat Central Arkansas 99-56 on Sunday. Van Slyke made nine of his 11 shots to help Arkansas State (3-2) end a two-game skid. Melvin Johnson III added 17. The Red Wolves made 30 of their 61 shots, including 7 of 18 from behind the 3-point line. Lenell Brown scored 12 points and was the only Central Arkansas (1-3) player to reach double figures. The Bears were held to 35 percent shooting. Arkansas State forced 24 turnovers, won the battle on the boards (48-26), and attempted 40 free throws compared to eight for Central Arkansas. Arkansas State has now won four in a row against Central Arkansas and leads the all-time series 21-18. In the previous six meetings, Arkansas State scored an average of 66.2 points per game.
